// deploy/presets.custom.jsonc — OPTIONAL operator preset overlay.
//
// Copy this file to `deploy/presets.custom.jsonc` (gitignored) and edit it to
// override or add LLM presets WITHOUT editing the package. It is MERGED over
// the bundled catalogue (bp_router/llm/presets_catalog.jsonc):
//   - a custom entry whose `name` collides with a built-in WINS (replaces it),
//   - a new `name` is added,
//   - base order is preserved; overlay-only names are appended.
//
// HEADS UP — scripts/prod.sh GENERATES this file for a hosted provider, with a
// `default` + `default_embedding` repointed at your chosen provider (and the
// embedding width pinned). Its output starts with a "GENERATED by scripts/
// prod.sh" marker line, which prod.sh treats as safe to regenerate. If you
// hand-edit the file (the marker is gone), prod.sh will NOT clobber it — it
// writes its suggestion to deploy/presets.custom.jsonc.generated for you to
// merge. Prefer adding one-off presets in /admin (never re-synced) over editing
// a prod.sh-managed overlay.
//
// ── WHEN IT'S APPLIED: EVERY boot, and only the fields you LIST ────────────
// The overlay (and the bundled catalogue) is re-synced into the `llm_presets`
// table on EVERY router startup. Each entry is upserted and marked `managed`;
// any managed preset dropped from the catalogue + overlay is pruned.
//
// PINNED-FIELD RE-SYNC: an entry overwrites ONLY the fields it actually LISTS.
//   - A field you LIST is "pinned" — re-applied (and re-overwritten) every
//     boot. This is the DURABLE way to fix a value across the fleet.
//   - A field you OMIT is operator-owned — whatever the admin UI / DB holds
//     for it survives the re-sync (it is NOT reset to a default).
// So the usual split: pin model identity + credential (provider,
// concrete_model, api_key_ref) here, and leave policy fields (min_user_level,
// sampling defaults, description) OUT so operators tune them in the admin UI
// durably. Pin a policy field too only when you want it fixed everywhere.
//   - Editing THIS file changes a seeded deployment on the next restart, for
//     the fields it lists. Admin-CREATED presets (added via /admin,
//     `managed = FALSE`) are never touched by the sync.
// (This file's path is wired via ROUTER_LLM_PRESET_OVERLAY_PATH — set in
// docker-compose.prod.yml to /app/deploy/presets.custom.jsonc. Pointing a
// deployment at a different BASE catalogue instead uses
// ROUTER_LLM_PRESET_CATALOG_PATH.)
//
// JSONC: `//` and `/* */` comments allowed; NO trailing commas. The result
// after comment-stripping must be valid JSON. Each entry mirrors the `Preset`
// dataclass (bp_router/llm/presets.py). An UNKNOWN key or a missing REQUIRED
// field fails LOUD at boot (a typo'd override won't silently no-op).
//
// ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//  FIELD REFERENCE  (✱ = required; everything else is optional with the
//                    default shown)
// ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
// ✱ name              The preset key agents resolve via
//                     ctx.llm.generate(preset="..."). Slug grammar
//                     ^[a-z][a-z0-9_-]{0,63}$ — lowercase, digits, `-`/`_`,
//                     ≤64 chars, NO dots (enforced by a DB CHECK constraint).
//                     Versions use `-`: name "gemini-2-5-pro" →
//                     concrete_model "gemini-2.5-pro".
//
// ✱ provider          Which adapter handles the call. One of:
//                       gemini | anthropic | openai | openai-embeddings |
//                       openai-compatible | openai-compatible-embeddings
//                     The `-embeddings` variants are for embed() calls; the
//                     `openai-compatible*` pair targets local/self-hosted
//                     servers speaking the OpenAI API (vLLM, LM Studio,
//                     llama.cpp-server, Ollama OpenAI-mode, TGI).
//
// ✱ concrete_model    The REAL upstream model id the provider SDK receives,
//                     KEEPING its native form incl. dots (e.g. "gemini-2.5-pro",
//                     "claude-sonnet-4-6", "gpt-5.5"). Unlike `name`, it is not
//                     slug-constrained.
//
//   api_key_ref       (default "") INDIRECT credential reference resolved at
//                     call time. Only the env://VAR scheme is wired: it reads
//                     the router container's environment. See the API KEYS
//                     section below. Empty + no inline api_key + a provider
//                     that needs auth → the call 401s.
//
//   api_key           (default null) INLINE literal secret. Takes precedence
//                     over api_key_ref when both are set. Stored PLAINTEXT in
//                     the DB (masked only on admin read-back) and sits
//                     plaintext in THIS file — see the caveat below.
//
//   base_url          (default null) Override the upstream endpoint.
//                       - hosted providers (gemini/anthropic/openai/
//                         openai-embeddings): OPTIONAL. Blank → the SDK's
//                         official URL. Set → a third-party server speaking
//                         that provider's API (MiniMax, Bedrock/Vertex mirrors,
//                         LiteLLM / Portkey gateways, enterprise auth proxies).
//                       - openai-compatible(-embeddings): REQUIRED — there is
//                         no official default to fall back to.
//                     Must be http:// or https://. SSRF-validated when saved
//                     via the admin API.
//
//   min_user_level    (default "*") Tier gate checked against the caller's
//                     level. Grammar ^(\*|admin|service|tier[0-9]+)$:
//                       "*"       any caller (no gate),
//                       "admin"   / "service"  exact-match that level,
//                       "tierN"   this tier OR stricter (lower N is stricter).
//                     Callers below the bar get PresetNotAllowedError.
//                     Like all policy fields: OMIT to let operators set the gate
//                     per preset in the admin UI (durably — including embedding
//                     presets); LIST it to pin one gate across the fleet.
//
//   description        (default null) Free text shown in the admin UI. Handy
//                     to record intent ("cheap bulk summariser", "EU-only").
//
//   default_temperature (default null) Sampling temperature applied when the
//                     call doesn't pass one. Range 0.0..2.0 (shared by
//                     OpenAI/Anthropic/Gemini). null → the provider's own
//                     default.
//
//   default_max_tokens (default null) Max output tokens when the call doesn't
//                     pass one. Positive integer (≥ 1); no fixed upper bound —
//                     it's model-specific. null → the provider's own default.
//
//   default_provider_options (default {}) Provider-specific knobs as a JSON
//                     object, e.g. an embedding width:
//                       { "output_dimensionality": 1536 }  // Gemini
//                       { "dimensions": 1536 }             // OpenAI(-compatible)
//                     NOTE: a call-time provider_options REPLACES this dict
//                     wholesale — it does NOT deep-merge. The bundled embedding
//                     presets no longer pin a width (the model emits its native
//                     dimension); if you pin one here, set SUITE_EMBEDDING_DIM
//                     to match or KB/memory writes fail.
//
//   fallback_preset   (default null) Name of the next preset to try once this
//                     one has exhausted max_retries+1 attempts. null → surface
//                     the error. Cycles are rejected at load time; a dangling
//                     name is treated as terminal (no further fallback).
//
//   max_retries       (default 0) Retry attempts on THIS preset before walking
//                     to fallback_preset. Integer 0..10 (capped to bound
//                     worst-case latency).
//
// ── API KEYS: `api_key_ref` (preferred) vs `api_key` (inline) ──────────────
// A preset gets its provider credential one of two ways:
//
//   api_key_ref  — an INDIRECT reference resolved at call time. The only
//                  scheme wired out of the box is env://VAR, which reads the
//                  router container's environment. The built-in provider keys
//                  already reach the container — just set their value in
//                  deploy/.env.prod:
//                    env://GEMINI_API_KEY, env://OPENAI_API_KEY,
//                    env://ANTHROPIC_API_KEY  (filled by scripts/prod.sh).
//                  For a CUSTOM / self-hosted provider, pick your OWN var name
//                  and add it to deploy/.env.prod.custom (KEY=value) — that file
//                  is injected into the router with no docker-compose edit. So
//                  env://MY_PROVIDER_KEY here + MY_PROVIDER_KEY=... in
//                  deploy/.env.prod.custom, done. A missing ref resolves to
//                  empty and calls 401. PREFERRED: only a reference lives in the
//                  DB/file.
//
//   api_key      — an INLINE literal secret. Takes precedence over api_key_ref
//                  when both are set. No env/compose edits — handy for a
//                  provider whose key isn't one of the three above, or a
//                  keyless local endpoint (use any dummy string). CAVEAT: it's
//                  stored PLAINTEXT in the llm_presets table (masked only on
//                  the admin API read-back, not at rest) and sits in plaintext
//                  in THIS file. Keep this file 0600 and off backups you don't
//                  trust. Avoid for shared/production secrets.
//
// Default below is an EMPTY array → a no-op overlay (safe to leave as-is).
// Example A — repoint `default` via an env ref (preferred):
//   {
//     "name": "default",
//     "provider": "openai-compatible",
//     "concrete_model": "qwen3:32b",
//     "api_key_ref": "env://OPENAI_API_KEY",
//     "base_url": "http://ollama:11434/v1",
//     "description": "Local Qwen via Ollama — overrides the bundled default."
//   }
// Example B — non-standard provider via your own custom key var (preferred; add
//             DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=... to deploy/.env.prod.custom, no compose edit):
//   {
//     "name": "default",
//     "provider": "openai-compatible",
//     "concrete_model": "deepseek-chat",
//     "api_key_ref": "env://DEEPSEEK_API_KEY",
//     "base_url": "https://api.deepseek.com/v1"
//   }
// Example C — same, but with an INLINE key (no env edit; plaintext in this file
//             + the DB — see the caveat above):
//   {
//     "name": "default",
//     "provider": "openai-compatible",
//     "concrete_model": "deepseek-chat",
//     "api_key": "sk-...",
//     "base_url": "https://api.deepseek.com/v1"
//   }
// Example D — pin extra fields on a built-in catalogue preset (cap tokens, add
//             a fallback) durably. The listed fields are re-applied every boot,
//             so they override any admin-UI edit; min_user_level is OMITTED
//             here, so operators still set the tier gate per deployment:
//   {
//     "name": "claude-opus",
//     "provider": "anthropic",
//     "concrete_model": "claude-opus-4-8",
//     "api_key_ref": "env://ANTHROPIC_API_KEY",
//     "default_max_tokens": 4096,
//     "fallback_preset": "claude-sonnet",
//     "max_retries": 2,
//     "description": "Opus with a token cap; falls back to Sonnet."
//   }
//   (Add "min_user_level": "tier1" to the entry too if you instead want to pin
//   the gate fleet-wide — then it overrides the admin UI on every boot.)
[
]
